---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
import Markdown from '../../../Markdown.astro';
import AIBalloon from '../../AIBalloon.astro';
import AIBalloonMessage from '../../AIBalloonMessage.astro';
import AIResponseMessage from '../../AIResponseMessage.astro';
import HighlightBox from '../../HighlightBox.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Progressive Disclosure and Information Prioritization"
  description="Surface what matters most first; reveal supporting detail or secondary information on demand so users aren't overwhelmed."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Progressive disclosure and prioritization" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>
          I received an order with two products, one of which is defective. How do I get a refund?
        </AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="progressive and prioritized" variant="success">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
1. Go to [My Orders](https://vittoriovittori.com/)
2. Select the order
3. Click [Request Refund](https://vittoriovittori.com/) next to the defective product

Want more details?

- **Timeframe:** Your refund will arrive within 5-7 days
- **Returns:** You may be asked to return the product
- **Evidence:** In some cases, a photo of the defect is required
        `}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>
          I received an order with two products, one of which is defective. How do I get a refund?
        </AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="everything at once" variant="error">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
To request a refund, go to the Orders section, select the product, choose the reason, and follow the wizard.

However, it's important to know that refund processing times can vary between 5 and 10 business days depending on the payment method used and the seller's policies.

Furthermore, in some cases, you must return the defective product before the refund will be approved, and you may be required to upload images demonstrating the defect.

Return policies may also vary depending on the product category and origin of the product.

Some sellers offer replacements instead of refunds, while others charge the customer shipping costs, unless otherwise stated.

We therefore recommend that you read the terms and conditions carefully before proceeding.
        `}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Lead with the answer, summary, or next step; put supporting detail behind "Show more" or
      expandable sections.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Present long reasoning, citations, and metrics before the user sees the main result.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Order information by importance to the user's goal (e.g. "what to do" before "why").
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Treat all information as equal; avoid burying the key takeaway in the middle or end.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
